<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/4568901-avid">Avid</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">There were some graphic scenes; however, i thought they were depicted responsibly and realistically in order to tell the story (the novel is based in <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">There were some graphic scenes; however, i thought they were depicted responsibly and realistically in order to tell the story (the novel is based in war-time west africa). I would not hesitate to have my 16-year-old read and discuss this book, although as with any book, there will be those with sensitivity to the topic. I think it can be a very important and valuable learning tool, and that outweighs, IMHO, many sensitivities to the graphic depictions that may arise. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
