<span id="freeTextContainer568115059836237339">November 2020 update: Winner of Winners of Women&apos;s Prize for Fiction, meaning the best book voted by the readers from all the previous winners. I think it is well deserved. <br/><br/>From this book you learn that the European powers did a shitty job when they created the African countries, not taking in consideration any cultural/tribe aspects. Lots of problems resulted from that, especially war. (Read 2013)</span>
  <span id="freeText568115059836237339" style="display:none">November 2020 update: Winner of Winners of Women's Prize for Fiction, meaning the best book voted by the readers from all the previous winners. I think it is well deserved. <br /><br />From this book you learn that the European powers did a shitty job when they created the African countries, not taking in consideration any cultural/tribe aspects. Lots of problems resulted from that, especially war. (Read 2013)</span>
